animal.description:
Hi, I’m Lolo! I’m a four-year-old, ten-pound male chihuahua, fully vetted, vaccinated, neutered, microchipped, and up-to-date on my heartworm preventative. You can call me Lolo the Lover, because I’m ready to bring the love and snuggles when you adopt me!

Do you like to cuddle? Do you have room for me to curl up in your lap? I love to be held! I’m also great at giving kisses, so pucker up! I get along great with kids and other dogs too, so I won’t mind sharing the love.

The only thing I don’t like to share is food. I’m still worried that I won’t get enough, so I can be aggressive when I feel someone is honing in on my meals. If you feed me by myself, I’ll be just fine!

They say all you need is love, but I like to think all you need is love and Lolo! You can never have too many snuggles, so what are you waiting for? Fill out an application today and get ready for a little more--no, a lot more--love in your life!

If you are interested in adopting Lolo, please DO NOT SEND A MESSAGE TO OUR RESCUE GROUP.  We are too busy placing dogs in great homes to answer messages and inquiries through the listing site.  

PLEASE GO TO THE LINK BELOW TO COMPLETE AN ADOPTION APPLICATION.
 
www.chihuahua-rescue.com/adoption-application
 
CRT requires an approved adoption application and a home visit for all adoption applicants.  CRT transports to OH, KY, IL, MI, MN, WI.

animal.description:
Sambria von Soest is a beautiful 18 month old German Shepherd.  Sambria and Weiss are very attached and want to be adopted together.  This is a story  about two young parents who were raising a family and suddenly found their world uprooted. Fortunately, Westside was there for them. Sambria, as might be expected, is unsure of her new surroundings and is hesitant at first to interact, looking back over her shoulder for Weiss and the reassurance she has in his presence. When she is comfortable, her sweet and sensitive personality comes out and she responds nicely to gentle affection.  Evaluated in playgroup, Sambria seems to have a medium energy. She is great off leash, curious about the environment and all the other dogs around. With Weiss at her side, she socializes graciously within the pack. Sambria and Weiss are looking for a happy-ever-after home where they can remain together.

animal.description:
Maggie von Maintal is a delightful 7 month old Shepherd mix.  Already over 75lbs, she'll be quite large when fully grown. Out of the gate of her kennel, this darling girl shows off her bright, joyful personality. She is eager to experience life and whatever is coming next. While she pulls a bit on her leash, she'll slow down with a reminder that there’s no hurry and she won’t be late to the party.  She does very well meeting and walking with her new pup friends. Off leash, joining playgroups, she comes in with high expectations of good fun and pleasant companionship. She makes her rounds, exploring her new surroundings and meeting every dog with a wagging tail. She loves to be the object of your full attention and affection and will cover you with kisses, if allowed.  She is content to take a break from her busy social life and sit right next to you, where she can observe the antics of her new friends and plan her next party.

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Layla and man have I had a year! Though I am a young girl, I came to my foster as a momma to a litter of puppies and I believe I have been a fantastic momma though I am very young. Being a young mom, I didn't have long to be a puppy myself and now? I am learning to play and have fun!

Now, I am a nervous girl but I just want to be loved and cuddled like any other dog. I would probably do better in a home without little kids as being nervous means I may startle easily. Of course, being a nervous dog means I need someone who is patient with me. Once I relax, I will reward you with a very dedicated dog that will love you. Dogs like me give the best rewards with love and affection!

I love other dogs as long they do not frighten me. I am not totally sure what scares me about them, but when they scare me, I bark, run, or I get as small as possible. I have shown no fear aggression and I don't know how I feel about cats.

I am a very sweet girl though and I love to play! I love being outside and will need a fenced in yard to keep me safe.

If you are interested in me, you may submit an adoption application at savingdeathrowdogs.com to learn more about me.

animal.description:
Breed: Springer Spaniel mix
Sex: Female
DOB: ~01/11/2008
Weight: 25 lbs (emaciated!)
Energy Level: Low
Personality Type: Low-Key, Lazy, Quiet, Gentle, Affectionate, Easygoing
History: Transferred from another shelter
Good With: Dogs, Kids 8+ years
Ideal Home: Any home looking to give a senior dog a place to live out her golden years!
Fence Requirements: None
Special Info:

The information we are providing for this animal was developed based on observations and assessments in a shelter or foster environment. We do our best to provide information that will help determine if the dog might be a good fit for you. Please note that behaviors may change in a home environment. We also ask our applicants to assume that any animal they adopt from us will need to be potty trained and learn house manners, although this is not always the case. Our online animal bios are designed to provide as much information as possible and answer some anticipated questions. We do not have the resources to respond to emails with more specific questions.

We are receiving an unusually high number of applications per pet at this time! Please follow the rules below to ensure your application is reviewed; pay attention closely to these instructions because applications will NOT be processed if they are not followed. Please keep in mind that dog/cat availability is currently changing by the hour; you will receive an email if the animal you are interested in is no longer available. New dogs become available almost every day, so feel free to let us know if someone else interests you if your initial choice is already adopted! 

Fill out the application (DOG: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IHD-DOG-Application-9-10-18.pdf, CAT: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/IHD-CAT-Application.pdf) completely. Every question must be answered, and it must be signed. If you are going to type your responses, open the application, save it, type your answers, and save it again. 

-Applicants must be 21+ years old and live within a 50-mile radius of our shelter at 22415 Groesbeck Hwy, Warren 48089.

-You must identify at least 1 dog/cat that you are interested in. If there are multiple dogs/cats, number them in order of priority. 

-Scan a copy of proof of home ownership (i.e. tax bill, deed, or mortgage payment - you can black out the account #, etc.) or animal clause/agreement of your rental agreement.

-Attach the application and home ownership proof/rental agreement animal clause to a new email and send it to bark@iheartdogs.org. The subject line must be formatted to read ""#1 choice of dog/cat, Your First and Last Name"". Example: Subject: Fido, Jane Doe
Once your application is received, it will be assigned to an Adoption Counselor who will follow-up with the applicant who is the best fit within a few days, or to discuss other dogs/cats. It could take up to a couple of weeks for you to receive a final disposition on your application so there is no need to check on the status.

-Introductions will be scheduled by appointment only, 45 minutes per appointment. The entire household, including current dogs, must be present for the appointment. The introductions will take place outside in our parking lot.

-We will continue to perform vet checks for current and prior pets in the household.

-Home visits will be in person for the yard and virtual for inside the home.

-Finalizing the adoption will also be scheduled by appointment.

While this process may seem cumbersome, it is interim during COVID-19, and it is designed to help us respond to the volume of emails we receive every day. Since we are receiving a high volume of applications, please be patient if a dog/cat is no longer available. 

Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description:
Pinto Bean is simply the sweetest perfect lady. She's a ""people person"" in a lovable dog body. This mixed breed, two-year-old is about 50 lbs. of wiggles who would do well in any home. She appears to know some commands and is eager to learn more as she settles into a life of fun and friendship. Pinto Bean has tested positive for heartworm, but FAMD does cover the cost of the treatment. Make an appointment to meet our very special Pinto Bean! All of our dogs and puppies go home spayed/neutered, microchipped, heartworm tested (if at least 7 months old), and up to date on age-appropriate vaccinations. We do our best to update information on adoptable pets as frequently as we can. If you're interested in a specific pet, we recommend that you call the shelter and ask if he or she still is available. Adoption questionnaires are processed in the order in which they're received.
For current adoption fees, please see our website, www.dearbornanimals.org. Adoption fee includes: age-appropriate vaccinations, spay or neuter, microchip, ID tag, fecal / worming, basic physical and behavior assessment. Dogs (6 months and older) receive an occult heartworm test. For an additional $20, cats (12 weeks and older) can be tested for FIV (feline immunodeficiency virus) / FLV (feline leukemia).

animal.description:
All people inquiring about pets listed as Courtesy Listings on the EAPL website and/or EAPL posting adoption boards should contact the current pet owner/rescue/shelter for answers to any questions and for final approval and placement. Please DO NOT CONTACT EAPL about courtesy listings. The pet owner/rescue/shelter and new owner shall make all arrangements on transferring the pet, information on history, vaccines, etc.
Hi! My name is Lucky. I am a nine-year-old Lab/Staffy mix female. But don't let my age or gray hair fool you. I love to play, chew on Kongs, go on long walks and even still run for a tiny bit when I can. Belly rubs are my absolute favorite! I can't get enough. I will just roll over for any human I meet and wait for my rubs. I also like to snuggle up next to you at the end of the day and just relax. I am ready to be an 'only fur child' of the house and receive all the love and attention that I can get and not have to share. I am told that I am pretty smart too and I know several tricks.

The ideal family for Lucky would be a home with adults who can still be active for her, no other pets and older children if there are still kids at home.
If you are interested in more info on me please reach out to the info below!
Kayla Gilmore
505-280-2227
Kayla.j.gilmore@gmail.com

animal.description:
***All animals listed on our website are in private foster homes. To arrange a meet and greet with a dog, you MUST fill out the adoption application so that it can be sent to the foster parent for review to determine if your home is a match for the dog. If a dog receives multiple applications, we operate on a best-fit basis, not first come first served.***


Hi! My name is Chanel and I am a 6-8 year old flat coated retriever mix. I've been called Tigger because I'm cheerful, outgoing, and bounce up and down on my back legs when I'm excited. I weigh around 45 pounds. I could probably weigh up to 50, but I shouldn't get any bigger than that! I am not typically a cuddly dog. I know better than to jump on the bed or couch and when I'm sleepy and want to lounge I'm just as happy to lay down a few feet away from you. I do like being pet and getting a belly rub on occasion. Rather than affection, I'd rather receive love in attention and food. I'm always hungry for a treat and only play with toys that feed me. With enough practice I might be able to set the record for cleaning out a frozen peanut butter Kong! 
 Because I am very food driven and smart, I have a lot of potential to learn tricks and new skills. I can already sit and lay down like a pro, and have been practicing ""shake"" and ""stay"" recently. I have some hearing loss so I'm learning hand signs along with commands, but luckily my ears don't slow me down at all. 
 I am a medium to high energy gal and do well with lots of exercise. I walk very well on leash and love going for walks. I typically walk 2 miles a day and could go much farther. I would be very happy with a family that likes to hike and maybe even run. While I'd enjoy a house with a big yard, I have a hard time occupying myself alone outside so having that structured exercise with my family is very important to me. 
 I have general anxiety that makes it hard for me to stay calm and I have been jokingly called ""high maintenance"". I like to nap in the morning but can spend the afternoon and evening panting and pacing around looking for food and attention. Sometimes if I don't get what I want I will throw a fit and bark at my foster dad, so I need a family that will be strict enough to help me learn that's not ok. I take Trazodone to help me stay calm but can still get overstimulated or anxious and it's hard to tell what my trigger is. I am most anxious if I feel separated from my family including crated or gated in a single room. I am house trained and not destructive and I'm looking for a home that does not plan to crate me. I can go in the crate, but it causes me a lot of anxiety and I whine and bark when I'm in there. I also insist on sleeping next to my foster dad's bed every night and don't like to be alone at night. Because of my anxiety, I would be happiest in a house without close neighbors in case I bark and a family that is home a lot or will take me out with them. 
 I am very friendly with strangers and seem friendly with other dogs as well. I want to talk to every dog I see while on a walk and had lots of fun meeting new dogs at the dog park. I have lived with other dogs in the past but have not been face to face with a cat. When I have seen them in their enclosures at the rescue I have not responded aggressively. I can be officially tested if requested! I have not been around children either, but I'm sure I'd be good with older kids that know how to respect animals.
 Overall, I am an adorable, sweet dog, who's biggest issue is that she might love and miss her family too much and not know how to express it. I need a family who will be around and will be patient and consistent with me as I learn the rules of the house and establish a routine that helps me thrive.

Hi I'm Eddie! I'm six months old and about 40 pounds - but definitely still growing. I am very affectionate and love cuddles and kisses. I'm a quick learner and already know sit, wait, come, stay and potty. I have puppy energy, after enough stimulation I curl up right next to you on the couch. I like to guard my resources, though I'm getting better at that every day. My foster parents say I'm really good in the car, but I'm still working on leash training. I'm crate trained, but sometimes sleep in my own bed next to my foster parents at night. Sometimes I can be noisy, but it's only because I want to protect you! I'd be best in a family without young children. I must go to a cat free home. I love my doggy foster sister, but it would be ok if I was the only child in my new family. I'm looking for an experienced dog owner that can continue teaching me new tricks! 

I am neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations, microchipped, have been dewormed, and am current on my monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. My adoption fee is $300. If you think I could be the one for you, please fill out an adoption application on our website: www.secondchancenc.org. Thank you!

If Max sounds like your man, please fill out an application today.

animal.description: Knickerbocker was a stray at the shelter before hitching a ride to our facility for safety. Staff all fell in love with this handsome gent from the second he entered the building. Pretty hard not to; he's got the looks and charisma to melt any heart. ""Knickey B"" is quite special. He's tall and lanky, but has no qualms about laying his whole body right on top of an already established Pug pile. You know, to get more cushion for his afternoon nap. This sweetheart is just that; and he's great with his canine friends. Sometimes he'll follow a couple around the suite or ""talk"" by sniffing at them. He's got some hind-end weakness, so his tootsie's drag a bit when he walks, but don't let the imperfect gait fool you. Knickerbocker loves to walk and explore. He has quite the curious nose on that way-too-adorable face. If a scent has really peaked his interest, he'll get some speed going and start to trot like a horse! Anytime spent outdoors with you where he can grab some sun rays, will thrill him to pieces. Despite his age, our delightful friend still has lots of life left in him. Please consider inviting this special creature into your home and your heart.

animal.description:
Meet Blazer!!! Blazer is a beautiful 2 to 3 year old, 50 pound male, pointer and labrador retriever mix. He was found wandering the streets of town, alone, hungry and cold, but not shy. Blazer is an extrovert, never meeting a stranger. His exuberance and friendly nature is contagious. Yes, he is a little goofy but he is a happy kind of goofy and will keep you smiling with all his goofy antics. Blazer also loves to ""talk"" to you, speaking with hums when being scratched and little yelps when at play, plus, he will bark an announcement at visitors, whether it's a car pulling into your driveway or a deer spotted in the backyard. My mom would have referred to this particular job as her ""redneck security system"". Blazer is very playful and energetic so regular exercise and a few dog toys will help keep him out of mischief. If you are looking for a jogging partner, Blazer is your man. He gets along with other dogs very well after a slow introduction, especially with the ladies and considering how handsome he is, it's no wonder he considers himself a ladies man. Blazer also gets along with older children, his size and enthusiasm at play is a concern with small children and toddlers. He has a sweet nature and loves attention. He is fully vaccinated, neutered and heartworm negative. Blazer is looking for a family of his own to love with an active lifestyle and a home to settle into.
Thank you for your interest in a Sandi Paws Rescue, Inc. Please visit our site at sandipaws.org for more information on our organization or to fill out an application to adopt one of our pets. You can find information for volunteering o. our site as well.

animal.description:
This handsome big boy is Big Red, he is a Shepherd/Lab/Black Moth Cur possibly or simply a big friendly doggy. He was found roaming the streets by himself when taken to a very rural shelter. We offered to try to find this big fella a forever home here in WI so he doesn't have to live the shelter life anymore. He is friendly with people, loves everyone but recommend no small children since he may accidentally knock them down. And does great with other dogs with proper intro of course. He will need to relearn house and crate manners though since he has been residing at the shelter. He loves to go on walks but he likes to lead the way, so perhaps some more training on this as well. He loves to hang out and enjoy the weather or goof around with other dogs to bide the day away. He is now hoping he can find a real forever home to call his own now, he would love to be someone's sidekick and pal. If your looking for a friendly big fella like this an online application can be found at SandiPaws.org

I've been looking for love in all the wrong places!

NATURE
Other dogs: loves playing with others
Cats: curious about them but very little exposure
Kids: loves but can knock down small one
Adults: love attention, very energetic
Additional comments 

TRAINING
House broke: No but she doesn't mess up her kennel
Pad trained: only exposed to pads after spayed. She did well. 

Leash trained: Yes but also loves to run free

VACCINATIONS
UTD 
SPAYED

This sweet carefree girl has been living at a very rural shelter in Mississippi with not lots of chance of being adopted. We offered to help her find a loving forever home here in WI.
